#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:2
msgid "Working with local files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:4
msgid ""
"To build a local project in a Nix derivation, source files must be "
"accessible to its [`builder` executable](https://nix.dev/manual/nix/stable/"
"language/derivations#attr-builder). Since by default, the `builder` runs in "
"an [isolated environment](https://nix.dev/manual/nix/stable/command-ref/conf-"
"file.html#conf-sandbox) that only allows reading from the Nix store, the Nix "
"language has built-in features to copy local files to the store and expose "
"the resulting store paths."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:7
msgid "Using these features directly can be tricky however:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:9
msgid ""
"Coercion of paths to strings, such as the wide-spread pattern of `src = ./."
"`, makes the derivation dependent on the name of the current directory. "
"Furthermore, it always adds the entire directory to the store, including "
"unneeded files, which causes unnecessary new builds when they change."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:14
msgid ""
"The [`builtins.path`](https://nix.dev/manual/nix/stable/language/builtins."
"html#builtins-path) function (and equivalently [`lib.sources."
"cleanSourceWith`](https://nixos.org/manual/nixpkgs/stable/#function-library-"
"lib.sources.cleanSourceWith)) can address these problems. However, it's "
"often hard to express the desired path selection using the `filter` function "
"interface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:19
msgid ""
"In this tutorial you'll learn how to use the Nixpkgs [`lib.fileset` library]"
"(https://nixos.org/manual/nixpkgs/stable/#sec-functions-library-fileset) to "
"work with local files in derivations. It abstracts over built-in "
"functionality and offers a safer and more convenient interface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:22
msgid "File sets"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:24
msgid ""
"A _file set_ is a data type representing a collection of local files. File "
"sets can be created, composed, and manipulated with the various functions of "
"the library."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:27
msgid ""
"You can explore and learn about the library with [`nix repl`](https://nix."
"dev/manual/nix/stable/command-ref/new-cli/nix3-repl):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:29
msgid ""
"$ nix repl -f channel:nixos-23.11\n"
"...\n"
"nix-repl> fs = lib.fileset\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:35
msgid ""
"The [`trace`](https://nixos.org/manual/nixpkgs/stable/#function-library-lib."
"fileset.trace) function pretty-prints the files included in a given file set:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:37
msgid ""
"nix-repl> fs.trace ./. null\n"
"trace: /home/user (all files in directory)\n"
"null\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:43
msgid ""
"All functions that expect a file set for an argument can also accept a [path]"
"(https://nix.dev/manual/nix/stable/language/values#type-path). Such path "
"arguments are then [implicitly turned into sets](https://nixos.org/manual/"
"nixpkgs/stable/#sec-fileset-path-coercion) that contain _all_ files under "
"the given path. In the previous trace this is indicated by `(all files in "
"directory)`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:48
msgid ""
"The `trace` function pretty-prints its first argument and returns its second "
"argument. But since you often just need the pretty-printing in `nix repl`, "
"you can omit the second argument:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:51
msgid ""
"nix-repl> fs.trace ./.\n"
"trace: /home/user (all files in directory)\n"
"«lambda @ /nix/store/1czr278x24s3bl6qdnifpvm5z03wfi2p-nixpkgs-src/lib/"
"fileset/default.nix:555:8»\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:58
msgid ""
"Even though file sets conceptually contain local files, these files are "
"*never* added to the Nix store unless explicitly requested. Therefore you "
"don't have to worry as much about accidentally copying secrets into the "
"world-readable store."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:61
msgid ""
"In this example, although we pretty-printed the home directory, no files "
"were copied. This is in contrast to coercion of paths to strings such as in "
"`\"${./.}\"`, which copies the whole directory to the Nix store on "
"evaluation!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:66
msgid ""
"When using the [`flakes` and `nix-command` experimental features](https://"
"nix.dev/manual/nix/stable/command-ref/new-cli/nix3-flake), a local directory "
"within a Flake is always copied into the Nix store *completely* unless it is "
"a Git repository!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:70
msgid "This implicit coercion also works for files:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:72
msgid "$ touch some-file\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:76
msgid ""
"nix-repl> fs.trace ./some-file\n"
"trace: /home/user\n"
"trace: - some-file (regular)\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:82
msgid ""
"In addition to the included file, this also prints its [file type](https://"
"nix.dev/manual/nix/stable/language/builtins.html#builtins-readFileType)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:85
msgid "Example project"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:87
msgid ""
"To further experiment with the library, make a sample project. Create a new "
"directory, enter it, and set up `npins` to pin the Nixpkgs dependency:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:90
msgid ""
"$ mkdir fileset\n"
"$ cd fileset\n"
"$ nix-shell -p npins --run \"npins init --bare; npins add github nixos "
"nixpkgs --branch nixos-23.11\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:96
msgid "Then create a `default.nix` file with the following contents:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:98
msgid "default.nix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:98
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  system ? builtins.currentSystem,\n"
"  sources ? import ./npins,\n"
"}:\n"
"let\n"
"  pkgs = import sources.nixpkgs {\n"
"    config = { };\n"
"    overlays = [ ];\n"
"    inherit system;\n"
"  };\n"
"in\n"
"pkgs.callPackage ./build.nix { }"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:114
msgid "Add two source files to work with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:116
msgid ""
"$ echo hello > hello.txt\n"
"$ echo world > world.txt\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:121
msgid "Adding files to the Nix store"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:123
msgid ""
"Files in a given file set can be added to the Nix store with [`toSource`]"
"(https://nixos.org/manual/nixpkgs/stable/#function-library-lib.fileset."
"toSource). The argument to this function requires a `root` attribute to "
"determine which source directory to copy to the store. Only the files in the "
"`fileset` attribute are included in the result."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:127
msgid "Define `build.nix` as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:129
#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:178
#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:249
#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:305
#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:369
#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:415
#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:456
#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:539
#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:581
msgid "build.nix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:129
msgid ""
"{ stdenv, lib }:\n"
"let\n"
"  fs = lib.fileset;\n"
"  sourceFiles = ./hello.txt;\n"
"in\n"
"\n"
"fs.trace sourceFiles\n"
"\n"
"stdenv.mkDerivation {\n"
"  name = \"fileset\";\n"
"  src = fs.toSource {\n"
"    root = ./.;\n"
"    fileset = sourceFiles;\n"
"  };\n"
"  postInstall = ''\n"
"    mkdir $out\n"
"    cp -v hello.txt $out\n"
"  '';\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:152
msgid ""
"The call to `fs.trace` prints the file set that will be used as a derivation "
"input."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:154
msgid "Try building it:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:157
msgid "It will take a while to fetch Nixpkgs the first time around."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:160
msgid ""
"$ nix-build\n"
"trace: /home/user/fileset\n"
"trace: - hello.txt (regular)\n"
"this derivation will be built:\n"
"  /nix/store/3ci6avmjaijx5g8jhb218i183xi7bi2n-fileset.drv\n"
"...\n"
"'hello.txt' -> '/nix/store/sa4g6h13v0zbpfw6pzva860kp5aks44n-fileset/hello."
"txt'\n"
"...\n"
"/nix/store/sa4g6h13v0zbpfw6pzva860kp5aks44n-fileset\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:172
msgid ""
"But the real benefit of the file set library comes from its facilities for "
"composing file sets in different ways."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:174
msgid "Difference"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:176
msgid ""
"To be able to copy both files `hello.txt` and `world.txt` to the output, add "
"the whole project directory as a source again:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:178
msgid ""
" { stdenv, lib }:\n"
" let\n"
"   fs = lib.fileset;\n"
"-  sourceFiles = ./hello.txt;\n"
"+  sourceFiles = ./.;\n"
" in\n"
"\n"
" fs.trace sourceFiles\n"
"\n"
" stdenv.mkDerivation {\n"
"   name = \"fileset\";\n"
"   src = fs.toSource {\n"
"     root = ./.;\n"
"     fileset = sourceFiles;\n"
"   };\n"
"   postInstall = ''\n"
"     mkdir $out\n"
"-    cp -v hello.txt $out\n"
"+    cp -v {hello,world}.txt $out\n"
"   '';\n"
" }"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:203
#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:382
msgid "This will work as expected:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:205
msgid ""
"$ nix-build\n"
"trace: /home/user/fileset (all files in directory)\n"
"this derivation will be built:\n"
"  /nix/store/fsihp8872vv9ngbkc7si5jcbigs81727-fileset.drv\n"
"...\n"
"'hello.txt' -> '/nix/store/wmsxfgbylagmf033nkazr3qfc96y7mwk-fileset/hello."
"txt'\n"
"'world.txt' -> '/nix/store/wmsxfgbylagmf033nkazr3qfc96y7mwk-fileset/world."
"txt'\n"
"...\n"
"/nix/store/wmsxfgbylagmf033nkazr3qfc96y7mwk-fileset\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:217
msgid ""
"However, if you run `nix-build` again, the output path will be different!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:219
msgid ""
"$ nix-build\n"
"trace: /home/user/fileset (all files in directory)\n"
"this derivation will be built:\n"
"  /nix/store/nlh7ismrf27xsnl3m20vfz6rvwlbbbca-fileset.drv\n"
"...\n"
"'hello.txt' -> '/nix/store/xknflcvjaa8dj6a6vkg629zmcrgz10rh-fileset/hello."
"txt'\n"
"'world.txt' -> '/nix/store/xknflcvjaa8dj6a6vkg629zmcrgz10rh-fileset/world."
"txt'\n"
"...\n"
"/nix/store/xknflcvjaa8dj6a6vkg629zmcrgz10rh-fileset\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:231
msgid ""
"The problem here is that `nix-build` by default creates a `result` symlink "
"in the working directory, which points to the store path just produced:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:233
msgid ""
"$ ls -l result\n"
"result -> /nix/store/xknflcvjaa8dj6a6vkg629zmcrgz10rh-fileset\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:238
msgid ""
"Since `src` refers to the whole directory, and its contents change when `nix-"
"build` succeeds, Nix will have to start over every time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:241
msgid ""
"This will also happen without the file set library, e.g. when setting `src "
"= ./.;` directly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:244
msgid ""
"The [`difference`](https://nixos.org/manual/nixpkgs/stable/#function-library-"
"lib.fileset.difference) function subtracts one file set from another. The "
"result is a new file set that contains all files from the first argument "
"that aren't in the second argument."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:247
msgid ""
"Use it to filter out `./result` by changing the `sourceFiles` definition:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:249
msgid ""
" { stdenv, lib }:\n"
" let\n"
"   fs = lib.fileset;\n"
"-  sourceFiles = ./.;\n"
"+  sourceFiles = fs.difference ./. ./result;\n"
" in"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:259
msgid ""
"Building this, the file set library will specify which files are taken from "
"the directory:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:261
msgid ""
"$ nix-build\n"
"trace: /home/user/fileset\n"
"trace: - build.nix (regular)\n"
"trace: - default.nix (regular)\n"
"trace: - hello.txt (regular)\n"
"trace: - npins (all files in directory)\n"
"trace: - world.txt (regular)\n"
"this derivation will be built:\n"
"  /nix/store/zr19bv51085zz005yk7pw4s9sglmafvn-fileset.drv\n"
"...\n"
"'hello.txt' -> '/nix/store/vhyhk6ij39gjapqavz1j1x3zbiy3qc1a-fileset/hello."
"txt'\n"
"'world.txt' -> '/nix/store/vhyhk6ij39gjapqavz1j1x3zbiy3qc1a-fileset/world."
"txt'\n"
"...\n"
"/nix/store/vhyhk6ij39gjapqavz1j1x3zbiy3qc1a-fileset\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:278
msgid "An attempt to repeat the build will re-use the existing store path:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:280
#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:328
msgid ""
"$ nix-build\n"
"trace: /home/user/fileset\n"
"trace: - build.nix (regular)\n"
"trace: - default.nix (regular)\n"
"trace: - hello.txt (regular)\n"
"trace: - npins (all files in directory)\n"
"trace: - world.txt (regular)\n"
"/nix/store/vhyhk6ij39gjapqavz1j1x3zbiy3qc1a-fileset\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:291
msgid "Missing files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:293
msgid "Removing the `./result` symlink creates a new problem, though:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:295
msgid ""
"$ rm result\n"
"$ nix-build\n"
"error: lib.fileset.difference: Second argument (negative set)\n"
"  (/home/user/fileset/result) is a path that does not exist.\n"
"  To create a file set from a path that may not exist, use `lib.fileset."
"maybeMissing`.\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:303
msgid ""
"Follow the instructions in the error message, and use [`maybeMissing`]"
"(https://nixos.org/manual/nixpkgs/stable/#function-library-lib.fileset."
"maybeMissing) to create a file set from a path that may not exist (in which "
"case the file set will be empty):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:305
msgid ""
" { stdenv, lib }:\n"
" let\n"
"   fs = lib.fileset;\n"
"-  sourceFiles = fs.difference ./. ./result;\n"
"+  sourceFiles = fs.difference ./. (fs.maybeMissing ./result);\n"
" in"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:315
msgid ""
"This now works, using the whole directory since `./result` is not present:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:317
msgid ""
"$ nix-build\n"
"trace: /home/user/fileset (all files in directory)\n"
"this derivation will be built:\n"
"  /nix/store/zr19bv51085zz005yk7pw4s9sglmafvn-fileset.drv\n"
"...\n"
"/nix/store/vhyhk6ij39gjapqavz1j1x3zbiy3qc1a-fileset\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:326
msgid ""
"Another build attempt will produce a different trace, but the same output "
"path:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:339
msgid "Union (explicitly exclude files)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:341
msgid ""
"There is still a problem: Changing _any_ of the included files causes the "
"derivation to be built again, even though it doesn't depend on those files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:344
msgid "Append an empty line to `build.nix`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:346
#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:397
msgid "$ echo >> build.nix\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:350
msgid "Again, Nix will start from scratch:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:352
msgid ""
"$ nix-build\n"
"trace: /home/user/fileset\n"
"trace: - default.nix (regular)\n"
"trace: - npins (all files in directory)\n"
"trace: - build.nix (regular)\n"
"trace: - string.txt (regular)\n"
"this derivation will be built:\n"
"  /nix/store/zmgpqlpfz2jq0w9rdacsnpx8ni4n77cn-filesets.drv\n"
"...\n"
"/nix/store/6pffjljjy3c7kla60nljk3fad4q4kkzn-filesets\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:365
msgid ""
"One way to fix this is to use [`unions`](https://nixos.org/manual/nixpkgs/"
"stable/#function-library-lib.fileset.unions)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:367
msgid ""
"Create a file set containing a union of the files to exclude (`fs.unions "
"[ ... ]`), and subtract it (`difference`) from the complete directory (`./."
"`):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:369
msgid ""
"  sourceFiles =\n"
"    fs.difference\n"
"      ./.\n"
"      (fs.unions [\n"
"        (fs.maybeMissing ./result)\n"
"        ./default.nix\n"
"        ./build.nix\n"
"        ./npins\n"
"      ]);"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:384
msgid ""
"$ nix-build\n"
"trace: /home/user/fileset\n"
"trace: - hello.txt (regular)\n"
"trace: - world.txt (regular)\n"
"this derivation will be built:\n"
"  /nix/store/gr2hw3gdjc28fmv0as1ikpj7lya4r51f-fileset.drv\n"
"...\n"
"/nix/store/ckn40y7hgqphhbhyrq64h9r6rvdh973r-fileset\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:395
msgid ""
"Changing any of the excluded files now doesn't necessarily cause a new build "
"anymore:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:401
#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:431
msgid ""
"$ nix-build\n"
"trace: /home/user/fileset\n"
"trace: - hello.txt (regular)\n"
"trace: - world.txt (regular)\n"
"/nix/store/ckn40y7hgqphhbhyrq64h9r6rvdh973r-fileset\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:409
msgid "Filter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:411
msgid ""
"The [`fileFilter`](https://nixos.org/manual/nixpkgs/stable/#function-library-"
"lib.fileset.fileFilter) function allows filtering file sets such that each "
"included file satisfies the given criteria."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:413
msgid "Use it to select all files with a name ending in `.nix`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:415
msgid ""
"   sourceFiles =\n"
"     fs.difference\n"
"       ./.\n"
"       (fs.unions [\n"
"         (fs.maybeMissing ./result)\n"
"-        ./default.nix\n"
"-        ./build.nix\n"
"+        (fs.fileFilter (file: file.hasExt \"nix\") ./.)\n"
"         ./npins\n"
"       ]);"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:429
msgid "This does not change the result, even if we add a new `.nix` file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:439
msgid ""
"Notably, the approach of using `difference ./.` explicitly selects the files "
"to _exclude_, which means that new files added to the source directory are "
"included by default. Depending on your project, this might be a better fit "
"than the alternative in the next section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:442
msgid "Union (explicitly include files)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:444
msgid ""
"To contrast the previous approach, `unions` can also be used to select only "
"the files to _include_. This means that new files added to the current "
"directory would be ignored by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:447
msgid "Create some additional files:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:449
msgid ""
"$ mkdir src\n"
"$ touch build.sh src/select.{c,h}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:454
msgid "Then create a file set from only the files to be included explicitly:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:456
msgid ""
"{ stdenv, lib }:\n"
"let\n"
"  fs = lib.fileset;\n"
"  sourceFiles = fs.unions [\n"
"    ./hello.txt\n"
"    ./world.txt\n"
"    ./build.sh\n"
"    (fs.fileFilter\n"
"      (file: file.hasExt \"c\" || file.hasExt \"h\")\n"
"      ./src\n"
"    )\n"
"  ];\n"
"in\n"
"\n"
"fs.trace sourceFiles\n"
"\n"
"stdenv.mkDerivation {\n"
"  name = \"fileset\";\n"
"  src = fs.toSource {\n"
"    root = ./.;\n"
"    fileset = sourceFiles;\n"
"  };\n"
"  postInstall = ''\n"
"    cp -vr . $out\n"
"  '';\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:486
msgid ""
"The `postInstall` script is simplified to rely on the sources to be pre-"
"filtered appropriately:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:488
msgid ""
"$ nix-build\n"
"trace: /home/user/fileset\n"
"trace: - build.sh (regular)\n"
"trace: - hello.txt (regular)\n"
"trace: - src (all files in directory)\n"
"trace: - world.txt (regular)\n"
"this derivation will be built:\n"
"  /nix/store/sjzkn07d6a4qfp60p6dc64pzvmmdafff-fileset.drv\n"
"...\n"
"'.' -> '/nix/store/zl4n1g6is4cmsqf02dci5b2h5zd0ia4r-fileset'\n"
"'./build.sh' -> '/nix/store/zl4n1g6is4cmsqf02dci5b2h5zd0ia4r-fileset/build."
"sh'\n"
"'./hello.txt' -> '/nix/store/zl4n1g6is4cmsqf02dci5b2h5zd0ia4r-fileset/hello."
"txt'\n"
"'./world.txt' -> '/nix/store/zl4n1g6is4cmsqf02dci5b2h5zd0ia4r-fileset/world."
"txt'\n"
"'./src' -> '/nix/store/zl4n1g6is4cmsqf02dci5b2h5zd0ia4r-fileset/src'\n"
"'./src/select.c' -> '/nix/store/zl4n1g6is4cmsqf02dci5b2h5zd0ia4r-fileset/src/"
"select.c'\n"
"'./src/select.h' -> '/nix/store/zl4n1g6is4cmsqf02dci5b2h5zd0ia4r-fileset/src/"
"select.h'\n"
"...\n"
"/nix/store/zl4n1g6is4cmsqf02dci5b2h5zd0ia4r-fileset\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:509
msgid "Only the specified files are used, even when a new one is added:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:511
msgid ""
"$ touch src/select.o README.md\n"
"\n"
"$ nix-build\n"
"trace: - build.sh (regular)\n"
"trace: - hello.txt (regular)\n"
"trace: - src\n"
"trace:   - select.c (regular)\n"
"trace:   - select.h (regular)\n"
"trace: - world.txt (regular)\n"
"/nix/store/zl4n1g6is4cmsqf02dci5b2h5zd0ia4r-fileset\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:524
msgid "Matching files tracked by Git"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:526
msgid ""
"If a directory is part of a Git repository, passing it to [`gitTracked`]"
"(https://nixos.org/manual/nixpkgs/stable/#function-library-lib.fileset."
"gitTracked) gives you a file set that only includes files tracked by Git."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:528
msgid ""
"Create a local Git repository and add all files except `src/select.o` and `./"
"result` to it:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:530
msgid ""
"$ git init\n"
"Initialized empty Git repository in /home/user/fileset/.git/\n"
"$ git add -A\n"
"$ git reset src/select.o result\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:537
msgid "Re-use this selection of files with `gitTracked`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:539
msgid "  sourceFiles = fs.gitTracked ./.;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:544
msgid "Build it again:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:546
msgid ""
"$ nix-build\n"
"warning: Git tree '/home/user/fileset' is dirty\n"
"trace: /home/vg/src/nix.dev/fileset\n"
"trace: - README.md (regular)\n"
"trace: - build.nix (regular)\n"
"trace: - build.sh (regular)\n"
"trace: - default.nix (regular)\n"
"trace: - hello.txt (regular)\n"
"trace: - npins (all files in directory)\n"
"trace: - src\n"
"trace:   - select.c (regular)\n"
"trace:   - select.h (regular)\n"
"trace: - world.txt (regular)\n"
"this derivation will be built:\n"
"  /nix/store/p9aw3fl5xcjbgg9yagykywvskzgrmk5y-fileset.drv\n"
"...\n"
"/nix/store/cw4bza1r27iimzrdbfl4yn5xr36d6k5l-fileset\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:566
msgid ""
"This includes too much though, as not all of these files are needed to build "
"the derivation as originally intended."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:569
msgid ""
"When using the [`flakes` and `nix-command` experimental features](https://"
"nix.dev/manual/nix/stable/command-ref/new-cli/nix3-flake), this function "
"isn't needed, because `nix build` by default only allows access to files "
"tracked by Git. However, in order to provide the same developer experience "
"for stable Nix, use of this function is nevertheless recommended."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:574
msgid "Intersection"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:576
msgid ""
"This is where `intersection` comes in. It allows creating a file set that "
"consists only of files that are in _both_ of two given file sets."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:579
msgid ""
"Select all files that are both tracked by Git *and* relevant for the build:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:581
msgid ""
"  sourceFiles =\n"
"    fs.intersection\n"
"      (fs.gitTracked ./.)\n"
"      (fs.unions [\n"
"        ./hello.txt\n"
"        ./world.txt\n"
"        ./build.sh\n"
"        ./src\n"
"      ]);"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:594
msgid ""
"This will produce the same output as in the other approach and therefore re-"
"use a previous build result:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/working-with-local-files.md:596
msgid ""
"$ nix-build\n"
"warning: Git tree '/home/user/fileset' is dirty\n"
"trace: - build.sh (regular)\n"
"trace: - hello.txt (regular)\n"
"trace: - src\n"
"trace:   - select.c (regular)\n"
"trace:   - select.h (regular)\n"
"trace: - world.txt (regular)\n"
"/nix/store/zl4n1g6is4cmsqf02dci5b2h5zd0ia4r-fileset\n"
msgstr ""

